The <#1242249109298221069> channel has daily training opportunities for how to support various efforts for the Presidential campaign. You should take your lead from that channel on any national election efforts. My social media approach has been trying the following. I stopped following any distractions, I'm currently only following people who I love to see succeed and those who lift me up. My first post was an honest video of myself letting folks know where I am emotionally and why it is important to me that I give this campaign my all. I use the posts from influencers I listen to with a supper short comment that connect the issue to future consequences and Kamala's  agenda and or qualifications. I dont know how to add pictures here so if you want to see an example you can see it on my instagram. thats the only platform i kinda know how to use so thats what im focusing on. t.mf.aidanator is my handle. its public so you dont have to follow me to see it.

Now im balancing that by sharing the funny stories that my friends send me via inbox. This achieves two things: my friends feel seen and I add some levity to the daily narrative. Im literally just copying the model that the DNC used.

Hi y'all - we had a GREAT in-person event in a rural and formerly very red area of our county yesterday, but where there are lots of cheaper housing developments going up and new families = some of them must be Democrats. We launched canvassing, had a party after at a Black owned restaurant, and had activities for kids like making Swiftie bracelets for voting, karaoke and the DNC playlist, had free pizzas, and lots of signs and enthusiasm. One guy yelled "Harris can kiss my hairy ass" as he drove away like a baby - we shouted back "she doesn't want to, honey!" but we got more honks of support than mad hollers. Apparently our Republican committee is freaking out and want to know how they can have more events in that shopping center (clutches pearls, faints on couch). Just to say - hang in there, and keep getting out there. One lady who came to the event said as a Black woman with opinions she feels like such a target, but coming to see she's not alone meant a lot to her. We had Black elders there too, and y'all, their stories. You, in your community, probably know someone who remembers having to pay a poll tax in Virginia. We're NOT GOING BACK!

Also, are you doing a "First Day of Early Voting" party Friday Sept 20? If you are, get them in Mobilize so other Dems can attend! Shout out Loudoun County is having a couple! Look for one near you üôÇ

Hey folks! Thank you for joining us. **Together, we will write the next chapter in the greatest story ever told.**

Phonebanking is our **number one priority** so close to the election, and it‚Äôs a phenomenal way to get started. We often set goals for specific numbers, like how we set a goal for 5 million calls this past weekend. We made 4.6 million, reaching immense numbers of people!

We‚Äôre 300,000 calls behind our goal for the day, and we urgently need to call Wisconsin voters. Early voting starts today in Wisconsin, and people need voting plans! We‚Äôre only **14 days away** from the election!

[Can we count on you to help us? Please, click here to get started and call directly into Wisconsin!](https://democrats.call.scaletowin.com/?t=32641249-daa7-4253-b97b-df11f362bdb3&ref=go_kh_calls_wi&utm_source=hfp_w_go_calls_20241022&utm_campaign=hfp_w_go_mb_do_vol_vrec_calls_20241022&utm_medium=go_kh_calls_20241022&utm_term=go_kh_calls_20241022)
